<br />
My speculation is that CV cap is just the damage done by your first hit, excluding crit and resist damage, multiplied by 10.<br />
<br />
EXAMPLE: if your first hit does 1500 before resist or crit then your cap would be 15k for that CV.<br />
<br />
I know I've capped out at 17-21k at times, then another time only cap at 13-16k and wonder what is going on.  This could be explained by perhaps being grouped with a psi and necro for a huge int boost in one case, and not in another, which would shift the base damage upward, thus having the same effect on CV cap.<br />
<br />
This is untested, it's just what I have percieved based on playing the game.  However, it shouldn't be too hard to put this to the test.<br />
<br />
It would also show us whether int/sdf/+%dmg gear may have the bonus of allowing us higher CV caps.
                  
