	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1139177">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1139177">
                  
                  Personally, I don't mind the fact that we lose a ring slot so much as I mind the fact that it's often a cumbersome / awkward / buggy implementation.  I don't know if we can still do it, but before the rings were soulbound we could summon 2 different ring types if we had one on a tombstone, then loot the tombstone and have 2 different ones.<br />
<br />
However, even if you put both of them on, you would still only get the buff from one.  Because of this, I don't understand why we aren't allowed to summon different types at the same time and swap them out as needed.  We can't switch them in combat anyway, so it's not really a balance issue, just an inconvenience.  It's not as big of a deal for me anymore since getting the Xenn lev cloak, but it was annoying as hell swapping between Quicksilver and Diamond rings before.  I don't really see what's unbalancing about having a different ring type sitting in your bag in case it's needed, and then switching to it while you're out of combat anyway.<br />
<br />
Take off the unique tags (well, there must be a special invisible tag too, since the rings actually ARE different... remove that too), and it'll take out some of the annoyance of our rings without breaking balance.  Fixing the bugs with the ring buffs would help quite a bit also, but I understand it's tied in heavily with the zoning issues that cause many other bugs as well and hopefully that will be fixed when the zoning issues are locked down.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
