		<div id="post_message_1140231">
                  
                  Can we get verification (although maybe wrong spot) that our summoned ring counts on VGPlayers or could somebody pass it along who could look into that?<br />
<br />
It appears in the &quot;inventory&quot; of our profile, but wearing the ring or not wearing the ring doesn't seem to change the stats listed.<br />
<br />
I don't think VGPlayers adds buffs to your stats, so it's all baseline+gear, however our ring is a buff AND gear at the same time. Can we please if taking a slot up, have it be accounted for in VGPlayers if it's equipped and showing there in the inventory as equipped?<br />
<br />
My stats are actually +37 int/wis higher because a slot doesn't seem to be getting counted where in game when wearing that item just the same, does count.<br />
<br />
Also, can we have the &quot;see invis&quot; ring looked into. <br />
<br />
We get that spell, so what is the purpose of that effect? <br />
<br />
Can we have something a little more useful, even if non-combat related (along lines of underwater breathing, levitate, etc)? Anything outside the box/cool that'd be nice to have come to mind that can be useful without being overpowered? Maybe something like 2-5% hate reduction when worn? This way it doesn't make solo overpowering but just another tool to consider (or something more useful than see invis anyways).<br />
<br />
Barrage IMHO needs a faster cast time on a side note.. right now it's not efficient, I can do other more effective things (aside from CV) in the time it takes barrage to cast for its energy and damage.<br />
<br />
Also, was in a group last night with a necro that was doing 380k dmg whenever a mob was like 40% every 30 minutes, can't we get something extreme on a 30 minute timer also being &quot;the most&quot; offensive/pure nuker in theory? Not class envy, just trying to figure out the logic in why we dont' have something along those lines (no meteor storm is hardly comparable given how situational it is).
                  
		</div>
